i have given up on art, and art has given up on me.  i spent the entire weekend trying to paint, the results were very discouraging.  I know forcing one to be creative does not produce great results, but even when i'm not forcing myself i chose to do nothing.  If you were to put a paint brush in my hand i wouldn't know the first thing to do.  

i have always said that art was fundamental to my existence, but now i feel like a fraud, only creating MAYBE one piece of art work per year. i feel even more phony when i am forced to discuss "my art" and my opinions on art/culture, i can talk the talk, my creative seems to shine as a con artist. i don't know if this is laziness, depression, or if i even had potential to begin with. My lack of confidence is really getting the worst of me, i have completed one class directed towards my area of study and i don't think i want to be a curator.  i don't know what i want to do, i don't know who i am, i feel like giant anonymous ninny who will die an indecisive raisin face.

I can honestly say with confidence that i do not like the internet. It is far too addictve and makes me self destructive.  I hate livejournal, i hate myspace, i hate msn.

I hate that they give the ability to read about people's lives (of times when i didn't know them or was in the process of getting to know them), Xpecially important people.  There are somethings you are better off not knowing, like hooking up with some girl or whatever stupid event happened.)

Listening to the latest cher album alone in my room would make me feel better than subjecting myself to such things on the internet.

thats all, i probably won't return after this. so i hope you have my phone number if you want to contact me.

I never thought i would ever say this, but i think i hate friday.  I am so happy that the "work" week is over, but i'm so tired...this sleepiness renders me a social retard. I yawn so much my eyes tear leaving me make-up less and squinty (Judy calls this DS FACE).   

friday equals casual day at work, which drives me nuts since i work with my mom and she doesn't like my casual clothes. she made me get changed before we left the house this morning and i cant stand what i am wearing which creates an instant un-confident heinous mood. 

the only boner about friday is i get to see my love nugget, the dry vag to this is that i'm too tired to express how happy and excited i truly am to get to see him. 

i don't get it, i used to be an over active insomniac, but now i can't wait to get to bed and just stay there for the rest of my life. i just want to go home. 

ps. i saw that you did call last night, i must have been comatose because my cell phone was beside my head on the pillow.

THIS IS MY NEW HAPPY HOME WITH MY NUGGINS + KITTEN.

I don't now how long this link will work for, but these are all the pictures and details:
http://www.viewit.ca/vwExpandView.aspx?ViT=14960

SPLASH, here is the discription.
The whole second floor of historical house built by Mayor of East Toronto. Two bedrooms or one bedroom plus den. It has been freshly painted and cleaned. The plumbing and wiring are all new. Electric service is 200 amps. All faucets are single lever mixing type. Good water pressure. Water service new right out to water main. First bedroom, ceiling fan with remote control and touch dimmer. Turn lights on from bed. View of deck and back yard. Second bedroom or den has exposed brick wall with tungsten halogen track lights with digital dimmer. Gas fireplace with digital electronic control. Living room bay window, switched outlets. Bathroom clawfoot tub, vanity, Toronto-approved toilet, pot lights, light bar for mirror and infrared overhead heat lamp for bathtub. Kitchen double sink, fridge and electric range, light over sink, ceiling fan with remote control, touch dimmer. Tungsten halogen lights on fan and track lights. Three large clothes closets. Private deck opens off kitchen convenient for barbecue. Lights on deck railing turn on with control. Dimmable bug light controlled from kitchen. Back yard gives view of five tennis courts in park. There are swings, kids play gym, splash pad, and dogs off-leash area. Parking is on interlocking brick lot off back yard. Car is visible from apartment. A complete recycling program is in place with grey and blue boxes, green bins, garden waste, racoon-proof garbage boxes and rain barrels. Sidewalk is lighted with theatre-style lights. Handy for streetcar, subway and GO train. GO train is 11 minutes to Union Station. Garage access is provided for bicycle storage. Motion sensors on outside lights. Lots of flowers.

I hate Mr.Sub. I don't know how they are still in business, eCspecially with Subway around.  I'm a little irritated right now, Mr.Sub was my only option today for lunch; i paid seven dollars for a crappy six inch sandwich made from bread that made paper seem more appealing, a tomato that tasted like genetically altered pumpkin guts and lettuce that looked like it came from my grandmother's compost heap...

i have to poo now and i only wish it was my lunch from five minutes ago because it is not worthy to stay in my body.

Life has become predictable and routine, as it tends to do.  However, school and a new apartment are around the corner. (Matt and I have yet to find a place we are both happy with--well one we can both afford)

I'm a little bit stressed out about next year, I won't qualify for a loan, and someone can only save so much.  I'm sure everything will work itself out, but i just keep thinking of expenses. I keep forgetting I have to eat. Maybe it would be cheaper to adopt a monkey and make my way through the streets of toronto like Aladdin and Apoo.

I can feel my body bloating with water and expanding with jelly beans, and chips, and pizza, and wine. I am on a new diet called eat whatever makes you feel good...Just don't expect to feel comfortable when you put on a form fitting skirt. 

Ugh, i feel my shit is hitting the fan....only to hit another, much larger fan.  Well at least it feels that messy and stinky--don't even get me started on the stink factor of my life right either.

It is so hard to feel positive first thing in the morning, EXSpecially when you have to call the love of your life to tell him you aren't coming down town to look at Andy Warhol stuff with him tonight.

Dinosaurs do exist, you could classify them as reptilian humanoids. Usually they attack in groups, which is funny because they tend not to care about anyone else but themselves. They are deceitful, and feed off good intention. I could really go on describing my take of a reptoid, but i think everyone who reads this has encountered one or two before. basically i hope that someday soon it is discovered that they are the reason the spread of stds is on an up rise, (because they are sluts in every aspect of the word) and from there they are quarantined on a desert island never to be heard of again. ////i feel like i'm going to puke, i have not felt so ridden with anxiety in a long time.

i am absolutely beside myself right now. i came home to find fritzy badly injured.  i didn't notice at first, but i got down on all fours to great him through the glass of my back door and i noticed a little bit of blood on his fur.  then i look at the deck and it looks like and episode of csi. there are blood splatters a foot long and thick drops surrounding my little sweet pea. i found the wound on his paw.

as of right now there is nothing i can do. he ran away on three cute legs, and his girlfriend/mother of his future kittens, poopie, followed. 

my parents don't seem to care. my dad was more upset that his blood was going to stain the deck.

i finally made it down town saturday night. the night had great potential until i got my period and became bed ridden with pain and nausea. i felt so awful, that i ruined the evening. matt assured me i didn't, but i wish i could have spent more time with him (consciously).

i have become 50% less stressed about school, i did a painting awhile ago at an art fag that fits my assignment perfectly. i only have one more assignment and a write up to do.

today was full of coffee and danishes; lounging on hills and swinging benches in a sun beam. leaving you is so hard, i miss you so much already. i can't wait to find myself in your arms again tomorrow night <3

well here is round 3...techinally speaking round 2 of the stomach flu.  

i cannot understand how someone can get the stomach flu twice in one month.  i woke up this morning feeling slightly nausiated. Before i knew it smelly runny poop and barf were everywhere/in the toilet!!

i was really looking forward to school, because not only does it mean learning, but it means i get to see matt, who i already miss so much its making the rest of my body hurt. i even attempted to get ready and was moments away from leaving, but i barfed...twice.  It was in that moment that i decided that it wouldn't be nice to vomit in some woman's hair due to the bumpy nature of bus transportation

this flu is making me feel over emotional and now i want to cry. i feel so weak. i think i need to slow down in general. i'm starting to feel like bilbo baggins when he starts blabbing about too much bread and not enough butter (being spread thin and not reaching the crust.)

honestly, just send me to the glue factory.

i should be doing homework right now, but instead i find myself updating livejournal and eating a red popsicle. i haven't updated in so long that i'm not really sure where to start...damn this popsicle is amazing...but not as amazing as my matty bobbins. i don't know if life can get any sweeter. i think i'm going to go sleep now...well, after writing my teacher a tragic email begging for an extension.

well...i'm pretty sure i just fucked up every good thing that was happening in my life in these past few days. i'm on that road of self destruction again pulling everything that gets in my way down with me.

i am so over whelmed with emotion that my body is physically protesting (or i am having an allergic reaction).  i cant cool down, my heart is racing, and i feel like i'm going to vomit.  my thoughts are whipping through my head so fast....oh god, the tears.

i am full of self doubt again. i feel like a total failure.

i can't stop thinking about the most incredible kiss i took part in on the weekend. wow. it was just creamy!

have a fabulous day everyone.
